### ListView Basics

`ListView` is a scrollable list of widgets arranged linearly. It is one of the most commonly used widgets in Flutter.

```dart
ListView(
  children: const [
    ListTile(title: Text('Item 1')),
    ListTile(title: Text('Item 2')),
    ListTile(title: Text('Item 3')),
  ],
)
```

### ListView Constructors

| Constructor | Use Case |
|-------------|----------|
| `ListView()` | Small, fixed number of children |
| `ListView.builder()` | Large or infinite lists (lazy) |
| `ListView.separated()` | Lists with separators |
| `ListView.custom()` | Custom children delegate |

### ListView.builder

For large lists, use `ListView.builder()` which builds items lazily as they scroll into view.

```dart
ListView.builder(
  itemCount: items.length,
  itemBuilder: (context, index) {
    return ListTile(
      leading: const Icon(Icons.star),
      title: Text('Item ${items[index]}'),
      onTap: () => print('Tapped $index'),
    );
  },
)
```

### ListTile Widget

`ListTile` is a specialized widget for list items with a consistent layout.

```dart
ListTile(
  leading: CircleAvatar(
    backgroundImage: NetworkImage(user.avatarUrl),
  ),
  title: Text(user.name),
  subtitle: Text(user.email),
  trailing: const Icon(Icons.chevron_right),
  onTap: () => navigateToProfile(user),
)
```

### ListView.separated

```dart
ListView.separated(
  itemCount: 10,
  separatorBuilder: (context, index) => const Divider(),
  itemBuilder: (context, index) => ListTile(
    title: Text('Item $index'),
  ),
)
```

### Scroll Controllers

```dart
class _MyListState extends State<MyList> {
  final _scrollController = ScrollController();

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    _scrollController.addListener(() {
      print('Scrolled to: ${_scrollController.offset}');
    });
  }

  @override
  void dispose() {
    _scrollController.dispose();
    super.dispose();
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return ListView.builder(
      controller: _scrollController,
      itemCount: 100,
      itemBuilder: (context, index) => ListTile(title: Text('Item $index')),
    );
  }
}
```

> **Key Point:** Use `ListView.builder()` for large datasets - it builds items lazily. Use `ListView.separated()` when you need dividers between items. Dispose of `ScrollController` in `dispose()`.

codeExample:
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

class ContactList extends StatelessWidget {
  const ContactList({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final contacts = [
      {'name': 'Alice', 'phone': '123-456-7890'},
      {'name': 'Bob', 'phone': '234-567-8901'},
      {'name': 'Charlie', 'phone': '345-678-9012'},
      {'name': 'Diana', 'phone': '456-789-0123'},
    ];

    return ListView.separated(
      itemCount: contacts.length,
      separatorBuilder: (_, __) => const Divider(),
      itemBuilder: (context, index) {
        return ListTile(
          leading: CircleAvatar(
            child: Text(contacts[index]['name']![0]),
          ),
          title: Text(contacts[index]['name']!),
          subtitle: Text(contacts[index]['phone']!),
          trailing: const Icon(Icons.phone),
          onTap: () => print('Call ${contacts[index]['name']}'),
        );
      },
    );
  }
}
